The Chairman of Kuje Area Council, Abdullahi Suleiman Sabo, has appointed Mr. Nagarta K. Yakubu as secretary of the council, and 13 other cabinet members. Sabo, in a statement he made available to newsmen, yesterday, named Adamu Haruna as supervisory councillor for Works and Suleiman  Buhari as supervisory councillor for Education. Others include Philemon Iya Gauge as supervisory councillor for Environment; Abisayi Bako as supervisory councillor for Agriculture; Yunusa Bona Abinallah as supervisory councillor for Health and Garba Monday as supervisory councillor for Special Duties. Others are, Abubakar Jibrin, senior special adviser on Education; Peter Bamayi, senior special adviser on Health; and Isah Zakari, senior special adviser on Special Duties. Tanko Baba Zagabutu, Isah Ada Alhasan and AbdulRaheem  Musa were appointed as senior special advisers on Works,  Environment and Political  respectively. Don’t leak official secrets, Kwali cabinet members warned Candido names 19-man cabinet Much is expected from you, Abaji boss tells cabinet members Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin